$ ORA-00922: missing or invalid option

{ Trailing semicolons

  One of the possible situation where the *ORA-00922: missing or invalid option* is thrown is demonstrated by the following example.
  The `create table` statement ends with a trailing semicolon which is not part of an SQL statement.
code {
begin
--
-- Note the traliing semicolon in the
-- SQL statement
--
   execute immediate '
      create table tq84_test_tab(a number);
   ';
end;
/
code }

  See also the error message â†’ development/databases/Oracle/errors/00933_SQL-command-not-properly-ended, which is sometimes raised when an SQL statement ends with a semicolon.

}
